    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY
        (FIGURE 77)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302177">FIGURE 77</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1302177" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302177" filename="../figg13/g1302177.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 77. Synchronizer Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the larger LO range synchronizer ring on the bench. Cover the assembly with a shop rag
                to prevent losing the three springs released from the high range synchronizer at the pin locations. Pull
                the HI range synchronizer from the blocker pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302178">Figure 78</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302178" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302178" filename="../figg13/g1302178.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Cover Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the three synchronizer springs and remove the HI range synchronizer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302179">left, Figure 79</hotlnk>). Remove the sliding clutch from the LO range
                synchronizer (right).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302179" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302179" filename="../figg13/g1302179.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. Synchronizer Springs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
